is a land sale—so </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">making the books balance by something that produces cash in year but does not change anything for future years?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Anita </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Charlesworth</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">The central</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> evidence is that these sort of—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">in the jargon</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">— </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">non</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#x2011;</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">recurrent</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">savings look to be growing as a proportion of people</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">s savings. The big one that people seem to use is holdin</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">g vacancies for a longer period, b</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">ut</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> while</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> you are increasingly concern</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">ed about your clinical staffing</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> that becomes a very difficult thing to do and is certainly not a sustainable productivity gain.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="f