 at best, frozen in real terms in the NHS</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> and reducing in </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">many parts of local government—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">is the core challenge across the health and care system</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> I would like to hear each of your views as to how we ar</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">e getting on with that process—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">both where we have got to but, more importantly, what it </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">will feel</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> like over the next two years and looking forward int</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">o the second half of the decade.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Matt Tee</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">It feels tough. </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">I would say that 20%</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> of our members say this is the worst financial situation they have seen in their time in the health service, and we have</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> some very long</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#x2011;</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">serving</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> people. So far, it feels to me</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">tha